<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910422-0179</DOCNO><DOCID>910422-0179.</DOCID><HL>   Credit Ratings:   Italy Debt Rating Under Review</HL><DATE>04/22/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><IN>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)INTERNATIONAL ECONOMIC NEWS AND STATISTICS (IEN)STOCK AND BOND RATINGS (RTG)</IN><NS>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)INTERNATIONAL ECONOMIC NEWS AND ANALYSIS (IEN)BOND andamp; STOCK RATINGS (RTG)</NS><RE>ITALY (ITA)</RE><LP>   NEW YORK -- Citing Italy's poor fiscal discipline andballooning deficits, Moody's Investors Service Inc. placedthe country's triple-A debt rating under review for apossible downgrade.   Consequently, the ratings concern also placed Italy'striple-A foreign-currency rating under review, as well as thetriple-A senior debt ratings of the state-owned companiesCariplo, Instituto Mobiliare Italiano and Crediop. Moody'swarned that Italy's failure to deal with its deficits couldhinder its goal of stable integration into a unified Europeanmarket. Italy's public-sector debt is higher than its grossnational product, Moody's said.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>